{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with butter and set aside.","Place butter into mixing bowl and melt <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place spring onions\/shallots into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add oil and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add spinach and cook <b>1 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>. Set aside in mixing bowl to cool for 10 minutes.","Add feta, ricotta, egg, salt and pepper and combine <b>15-20 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Set aside in mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 180°C.","Place 1 sheet of filo pastry onto a clean work surface, keeping remaining pastry covered with a clean, damp kitchen towel. Brush filo sheet with reserved melted butter. Place a second sheet on top, then brush with butter. Place a third sheet on top and brush with butter. Cut pastry into 3 strips (each 14 cm wide), then cut into halves (forming 14 cm x 13.5 cm rectangles).","Place 1 tablespoon of the reserved spinach mixture along bottom edge of each rectangle. Fold in side edges by 1 cm and brush with melted butter. Fold over end of pastry to overlap filling, then roll up, making sure edges are tucked inside and filling is sealed, forming a finger shape. Place seam side down onto prepared baking trays, leaving at least a 3 cm gap between each roll. Repeat with remaining pastry, filling and butter (makes approx. 36 fingers - see Tips).","Brush tops of fingers with melted butter and bake for 18-20 minutes (180°C), until lightly golden and crisp. Serve warm or at room temperature."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["180 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces (3 cm), plus extra for greasing","2 - 3 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into quarters","20 g olive oil","500 g frozen chopped spinach, thawed and excess moisture squeezed out (approx. 250 g after moisture removed)","200 g feta cheese, crumbled (see Tips)","250 g ricotta cheese, drained","1 egg","¼ - ½ tsp salt","2 pinches  ground black pepper","18 - 20 sheets filo pastry  (approx. 375 g)"]}],"id":"r138808","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-h7kwh3LjVAo\/XZaqqD0MsvI\/AAAAAAAAhfQ\/YHVVvG1JVP4Ahs9_3X-fb_SPprJW5xakgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_i0Bw-7XcGkR7HQUs.png","title":"Flaky filo fingers","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.7 g","fat":"7.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"4.6 g","calories":"406 kJ \/ 203 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), bowl, kitchen towel, pastry brush, oven","hintsAndTricks":["A firm (Australian) feta works best for this recipe.","Unbaked filo fingers can be placed into a freezable storage container and frozen for up to 3 weeks. They can be baked from frozen for 18-20 minutes (180°C), until lightly golden and crisp.","3 garlic cloves","1 brown onion (approx. 100 g), cut into quarters","100 g red capsicum, deseeded and cut into pieces","3 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","250 g each pork mince, beef mince and lamb mince","1 egg white","1 tsp salt, to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper, to taste","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","½ tsp paprika"],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 30m","36 portions"]}